comment: Express a function ` F ` whose value ` B ` may not always be a set in terms of another function ` G ` for which sethood is guaranteed. (Note that ` ( _I `` B ) ` is just shorthand for ` if ( B e. _V , B , (/) ) ` , and it is always a set by ~ fvex .) Note also that these functions are not the same; wherever ` B ( C ) ` is not a set, ` C ` is not in the domain of ` F ` (so it evaluates to the empty set), but ` C ` is in the domain of ` G ` , and ` G ( C ) ` is defined to be the empty set.
